Search for a tab character in a string:

Copy
let str = "Visit Demo2s.com.\tLearn JavaScript.";
let patt1 = /\t/;
let result = str.search(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \t metacharacter is used to find a tab character.

\t returns the position where the tab character was found.

If no match is found, it returns -1.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\t	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\t") or simply: /\t/
